The Director of the American Technology Council (ATC), Chris Liddell, discusses the report on the modernization of Federal Information Technology (IT) that was directed by the President through Executive Order (EO) 13800. The report was developed by experts selected by various government agencies and aims to create a vision for the future of Federal IT that maximizes the use of secure commercial technology and defines a plan to transition the government to that vision. The objectives of the vision include enabling faster delivery of new capabilities to the public, increasing cybersecurity, and operating IT in a more cost-effective manner. The report also addresses previous challenges in IT modernization, such as budget constraints, procurement issues, and outdated policies. The plan outlined in the report incorporates industry best practices and emphasizes a close partnership with industry to achieve the targeted vision. The government is seeking feedback from industry on the report, which can be submitted through the website provided.